    "last_edit_date" : 1329925240,
    "creation_date" : 1329923135,
    "answer_id" : 9397328,
    "question_id" : 9397203,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Look at the <code>getActualMaximum(int field)</code> method of the Calendar object.</p>\n\n<p>If you set your Calendar object to be in the month for which you are seeking the last date, then <code>getActualMaximum(Calendar.DAY_OF_MONTH)</code> will give you the last day.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 946,
      "reputation" : 18467,
      "user_id" : 1247,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 91,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/300b7053db5618b12cca22ba85652c95?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Mike Deck",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1247/mike-deck"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 22,
    "last_activity_date" : 1329923194,
    "creation_date" : 1329923194,
    "answer_id" : 9397347,
    "question_id" : 9397203,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can set the calendar to the first of next month and then subtract a day.</p>\n\n<pre><code>Calendar nextNotifTime = Calendar.getInstance();\nnextNotifTime.add(Calendar.MONTH, 1);\nnextNotifTime.set(Calendar.DATE, 1);\nnextNotifTime.add(Calendar.DATE, -1);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>After running this code nextNotifTime will be set to the last day of the current month.  Keep in mind if today is the last day of the month the net effect of this code is that the Calendar object remains unchanged.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1172973,
      "reputation" : 3278,
      "user_id" : 1149714,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 76,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/54eaae12a01bc8d9b0aa60ebe3dca45d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "yetAnotherSE",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1149714/yetanotherse"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 40,
    "last_activity_date" : 1350913714,
    "creation_date" : 1350913714,
    "answer_id" : 13012840,
    "question_id" : 9397203,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>And to get last day as Date object:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance();\ncal.set(Calendar.DATE, cal.getActualMaximum(Calendar.DATE));\n\nDate lastDayOfMonth = cal.getTime();\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
