      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Good Answer. But that last part is weak, suggesting the use of <code>LocalDateTime</code>. That class lacks any concept of time zone or offset-from-UTC. So it cannot determine when a particular day in a particular place actually starts. That class only works for plain generic 24-hour days, not real-world days. For real days, specify a time zone: <code>ZonedDateTime zdt = now.atStartOfDay( ZoneId.of( &quot;Asia&#47;Tokyo&quot; ) ) ;</code>. Some days in some places may start at a different time, such as 01:00, because of anomalies such as Daylight Saving Time (DST)."
    } ],
