    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<h1>java.time.temporal.TemporalAdjusters.lastDayOfMonth()</h1>\n<p>Using the <code>java.time</code> library built into Java 8, you can use the <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/time/temporal/TemporalAdjuster.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>TemporalAdjuster</code></a> interface. We find an implementation ready for use in the <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/time/temporal/TemporalAdjusters.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>TemporalAdjusters</code></a> utility class: <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/time/temporal/TemporalAdjusters.html#lastDayOfMonth()\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>lastDayOfMonth</code></a>.</p>\n<pre><code>import java.time.LocalDate;\nimport java.time.temporal.TemporalAdjusters;\n\nLocalDate now = LocalDate.now(); //2015-11-23\nLocalDate lastDay = now.with(TemporalAdjusters.lastDayOfMonth()); //2015-11-30\n</code></pre>\n<p>If you need to add time information, you may use any available <code>LocalDate</code> to <code>LocalDateTime</code> conversion like</p>\n<pre><code>lastDay.atStartOfDay(); //2015-11-30T00:00\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 73141,
      "reputation" : 11574,
      "user_id" : 210791,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 57,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a762671d1880f547cee648814621093a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "satnam",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/210791/satnam"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 10,
    "last_activity_date" : 1492018909,
    "creation_date" : 1492018909,
    "answer_id" : 43376239,
    "question_id" : 9397203,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Using the latest <code>java.time</code> library here is the best solution:</p>\n\n<pre><code>LocalDate date = LocalDate.now();\nLocalDate endOfMonth = date.with(TemporalAdjusters.lastDayOfMonth());\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Alternatively, you can do:</p>\n\n<pre><code>LocalDate endOfMonth = date.withDayOfMonth(date.lengthOfMonth());\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
